titl git-commit(1)

syno git commit [-m msg]

text The command that actually writes data into the git repository

item Commit what has previously been added
	ite2
		code git commit
item Add and commit
	ite2
		code git commit -a
item Commit with a message (oneliner)
	ite2
		code git commit -m "My commit message"
item Combine parameters
	ite2
		code git commit -a -m "My commit message"

text If you leave
	code -m
	then your EDITOR will be launched where you should write your commit message
